               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter, 20th. Varia: Ff. irv, the last 2 lines of iir, and <locus target="#142r"/>: Angels Praise Her, written in a different hand. F. iir, top: Excerpt from Image of Jesus Christ, Mälk‘a Iyyäsus, መልክአ፡ ኢየሱስ፡, and another similar text. F. iir, middle: List of the fasting times of the year. <locus target="#140v"/>-141v Personal prayer for ግብረ ጊዮርጊስ ጃረ based on lines from the Horlogium of Abba Giyorgis. F<locus target="#1r"/>-140v Psalter, beginning with the opening prayer from Psalter of the Virgin (1r). The midpoint is unmarked. Psalm 151 is the short version, with the longer text written in blue ink in the margin and between lines. The fourth biblical canticle has the word prophet in the base hand, but another hand has added a final ት, i.e., prophetess. The Song of Songs is the common edition. The Praises of Mary begin with Monday and culminate in Sunday. </summary>
